															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="1361261"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1416772563 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Nov 2014 19:56</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2164628">
									

<p>I'm glad I had the time to read this when I wasn't scrapping one contest entry concept and hurriedly trying to come up with another. The way in which this was handled, the long introspective narrative interposed with individual vignettes giving us an idea of the reality you're working with, was perfectly suited to the gravity of the subject material. The characters felt real in their short time with the reader, and the story unfolded in its own time.</p>
<p>The writing style was beautiful. It evoked a sort of feeling I get when I read 50s and 60s science fiction, when the genre was far braver and far more searing than I think it is today. This could have appeared in a <em>Dangerous Visions</em> anthology.</p>
<p>I suspect this was the entry that FFB referred to in his KaktusKast. Because barring any additional entries, I think this is our winner. Outstanding work, Reach.</p>

							</div>

								
					
