				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hammermaiden" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1552358); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1552358&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203728" alt="HammerMaiden" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1552358)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/hammermaiden" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1552358); return false;" >HammerMaiden</a></span> <span class="odate time_1416798988 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">24 Nov 2014 03:16</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2164833">
									

<p>You suspect correctly. He wouldn't believe me when I said it.</p>
<p>Here's why I said it:</p>
<ol>
<li>The presentation is excellent. There's just enough multimedia and CSS to break up the wall of text and give it a little visual pleasure without detracting from the work (or relying on the gimmick).</li>
<li>While the content itself isn't altogether original, nor the conclusion, the execution, as you've already pointed out, is flawless.</li>
<li>It is well polished in word choice and pacing. Even the few grammar errors and typos in it when I read the draft weren't enough to catch my attention or throw me off the thread.</li>
<li>Speaking of the thread, it is <em>strong</em>. The beginning hooks you with intrigue, the first vignette confuses you in just the right way, and before you know it, you've read all 5000 words and you're sorry it's over. The length is justified by the strength of the story.</li>
<li>It is the Foundation <em>reductio ad absurdum</em>, plain and simple. This is the logical conclusion of the Foundation's illogical premise: protect the status quo at <em>all</em> cost. That's where the title came from.</li>
<li>It perfectly fulfills the prompt. It wants nothing yet leaves us wanting.</li>
</ol>
<p>This is the shit that gets people noticed, and I'm happy that it's here.</p>
<p>+1</p>

