			<div class="content" id="post-content-2165156">
									

<p>I completely agree, and when I was reading the draft I couldn't help but think, &quot;Is this as good as I think it is? Because it feels like the sure winner.&quot;</p>
<p>The imagery is phenomenal without being overwritten. I can say without any hyperbole that the first vignette in this tale is the only thing I've ever read on this site that has given me shivers. And each one is very different, yet adds to the tale as much as any of the others. When I first skimmed over the draft, it all felt very daunting, but I was so glad I read it in its entirety. It deserves its current standing in the contest.</p>
<p>The only bad thing I have to say about it is that it takes a bit of the excitement out of the contest, lol. I didn't end up submitting my tale, mostly because I couldn't get a consensus on whether it felt finished or not, but it didn't help that I knew it couldn't possibly win with this entry in the running. That's not a complaint or criticism of this piece, or even meant to be self-deprecating; it's just the truth.</p>
<p>+1</p>

