		<div class="post" id="post-2166559">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2166559)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2166559">
																		Here, grab a wire.
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-reach" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1779895); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1779895&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610203728" alt="Dr Reach" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1779895)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dr-reach" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1779895); return false;" >Dr Reach</a></span> <span class="odate time_1416999251 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">26 Nov 2014 10:54</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2166559">
									

<p>Alright, here you go!</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">++&nbsp;Mission&nbsp;Statement&nbsp;spoilers.&nbsp;Avert&nbsp;your&nbsp;eyes!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">--&nbsp;This&nbsp;is&nbsp;a&nbsp;synopsis.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>Is the implication that the Foundation (&#8230;)</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Not exactly destroying, but the character feels that yes! The Foundation destroyed the universe, burned it and used it as bait to escape! Lemme review it;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>the universe was going to die.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The universe is being hunted by an extra-universal predator. The threat of such creature is so large that the Foundation can barely understand it, even when they have mastered FTL travel and conquered anomalies in Sol. In the Fleet section, there is this to say about this threat:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>And Sol, and all its promises, goes away in a stream of twisted space coiling on itself as it disappears. In its place, the universe slowly becomes darker, darker as the worlds the Exiles had visited, the worlds the Enemy had chosen to devour first. Darker as if a shadow came to them…</p>
<p>It had always been coming. It was here. The end of the universe. The thing that would have its prey.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>&quot;Spoilers&quot;: it's a predator universe hunting on our own. The way the process of devouring our universe appears to us, humans, is a shadow, a darkness.</p>
<p>In order to escape this fate, the Foundation makes a choice; screw the universe, we want to live.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>At the negligible cost of the rest of the universe, we escaped a threat that is now devouring all known space… perhaps all that once was, for lack of a better word, &quot;real.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is quite literal, since the Foundation is using Reality Anchors, arranged in a Dyson swarm (roughly a sphere) around Sol, because:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The Anchors we have deployed took almost a century of uninterrupted work to finish. They do keep at bay the simple horror of a predator that we, poor prey, are not evolved enough to outrun on our own.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>That is, Reality Anchors prevent the &quot;shadow&quot; from manifesting within Sol. To make certain this lasts, since Anchors are not necessarily 100%:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>There are dozens of temporal sinks beyond the Oort Cloud, their size larger than the Moon, continuously bartering time out of a universe that has none left for itself. They siphon what little eons can be salvaged from it.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The temporal sinks are based off SCP-2000's XACTS, devices that can slow the flow of time in a volume of space by stabilizing tachyon flow. However, this Foundation is using them to &quot;siphon&quot; time from the rest of the universe; essentially, we are &quot;bartering time out of a universe&quot; doomed to death, since the shadow will end it anyways, and thus &quot;has none (time) left for itself&quot;. The universe will run out of time much, much sooner as a consequence.</p>
<p>And, finally, to detach Sol from this universe and save us all, the Foundation &quot;physically&quot; separates us from the rest of the universe.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I try to imagine a teardrop as it detaches from the universe's face and drifts away.</p>
<p>Safe. Confined. Protected.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>As a result of this, the Foundation had the option to simply tell humanity nothing about the stars,</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The last wave of true starlight already passed Earth and I missed it. Stars have dulled, and most die out entirely as I look.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The last wave of starlight coming from the Border, which has been closed &quot;a few light-hours&quot; away, is only now coming to Earth; now, all sunlight is collected by the Dyson swarm, which uses it to power the Border and create the fake night sky.</p>
<p>Most of these things are implications. I didn't want to elaborate far too much on them, since focusing on the emotional and personal view of the narrator character and the various small snippets in here was far more important.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>We vowed to protect humanity. Intellectually, I know how morally myopic this all sounds, to sacrifice the entire universe as bait while we built our own defense, our Infinite Border.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>So I'll leave the moral implications for you to mull over. :3</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>tl;dr</strong></p>
<p>The Foundation knows the universe is ending and makes the choice to use bullshit tech to a) steal time from the rest of the otherwise doomed 'verse b) make sure whatever it is that the thing actually is doesn't follow and c) make things terribly complicated just so it keeps humanity from learning this, in order to maintain morale, normalcy and a future (closed and restricted as it is) for us.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

